<h2 align=center>
  MAS 100 Concepts of Mathematics Fall 2013<br>
  Grading Rubric for Essays and Presentations<br>
</h2>


<h3>Grading Rubric for Essays</h3>

<table border="1" cellpadding="10">

<!-- top row is point value headings -->
<tr>
<td>
</td>
<td align="center">4 <br>excellent
</td>
<td align="center">3 <br>good
</td>
<td align="center">2 <br>satisfactory
</td>
<td align="center">1 <br>meets requirements minimally
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Purpose 
</td>
</td>
<td>story has a clear goal; <br>purpose is excellent
</td>
<td>purpose is good
</td>
<td>purpose is satisfactory
</td>
<td>purpose is poor
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Critical Thinking
</td>
</td>
<td>storytelling reflects incisive, original<br>
critical thinking of the writer;<br>critical thinking is excellent
</td>
<td>critical thinking is good
</td>
<td>critical thinking is satisfactory
</td>
<td>critical thinking is poor
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Content
</td>
</td>
<td>content is excellent <br>in support of storytelling goal
</td>
<td>content is good
</td>
<td>content is satisfactory
</td>
<td>content is poor
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Energy
</td>
</td>
<td>storytelling is compelling and persuasive; <br>
enthusiasm is infectious;<br>
energy is excellent
</td>
<td>energy is good
</td>
<td>energy is satisfactory
</td>
<td>energy is poor
</td>

<tr>
<td>Organization and Structure
</td>
</td>
<td>main points and supporting points show clearly;<br>
transitions are clear;<br>organization and structure are excellent
</td>
<td>organization and structure are good
</td>
<td>organization and structure are satisfactory
</td>
<td>organization and structure are poor
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Mechanics:<br> grammar, syntax, spelling, format<br>
(includes bibliography)
</td>
</td>
<td>almost no flaws
</td>
<td>few flaws
</td>
<td>too many flaws to be "good"
</td>
<td>many flaws
</td>
</tr>


</table>

<h3>Grading Rubric for Presentations</h3>

In the grading rubric for essays, substitute the word "presentation" for
"writing" and "presenter" for "writer". Change the list after
"Mechanics" to "use of voice, body language, audio and visual aids,
technology".

